 <Header id="B">
  <h1>The Starter Code</h1>
 </Header><div>
  <p class="firstLine">
   The file <tt>person.h</tt> contains the definition of a <tt>Person</tt>
   structure, with <tt>name</tt>, <tt>email</tt> and
   <tt>phone</tt> data members, as well as the prototypes for some functions and
   operators.
  </p>
  <pre
   class="language-cpp"><code>struct Person&lbrace; 
	std::string name;
	std::string email;
	std::string phone;
&rbrace;;</code></pre>
  <p>
   The <tt>main()</tt> function <mark>creates an array</mark>
   of 1000 <tt>Person</tt> variables, and then calls the <tt>load()</tt> function
   to read all of the data from the text file and put it into the array.
  </p>
  <pre
   class="language-cpp"><code>const int kSize = 1000;
Person directory[kSize];
load(directory, kSize);</code></pre>
  <p>
   Following the array declaration is a <tt>do-while</tt> loop which asks the user
   for a last name, and which then calls the <tt>find()</tt> function to retrieve
   the record number.
  </p>
  <pre
   class="language-cpp"><code>bool done = false;
do&lbrace; 
  cout &lt;&lt; "Enter the last name to search for (q to quit): ";
  string last;
  cin &gt;&gt; last;
  if (last == "q") done = true;
  else
 &lbrace; 
    int pos = find(directory, kSize, last);
    if (pos &gt;= 0)&lbrace; 
      cout &lt;&lt; "\nFound: " &lt;&lt; directory[pos] &lt;&lt; endl;
    &rbrace; else&lbrace; 
      cout &lt;&lt; "\nCannot find " &lt;&lt; last &lt;&lt; endl;
   &rbrace; 
 &rbrace; 
&rbrace;
while (! done);</code></pre>
  <p>
   If the name is found in the directory, then the program prints out the full
   name, email and phone number. If the name could not be found, the program
   just prints "Not found" and allows the user to enter another name. The user
   can exit by entering "q" when asked for the last name.
  </p>
 </div>
